  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWhen going to Step 3 ([Start Another Beacon Node](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse#3-start-another-beacon-node)) in the readme simple testnet instructions, the second node fails due to a collision in the RestAPI port.\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe current behaviour is that `./beacon_node` defaults to having the Rest API enabled due to the following default config.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/c4ced3e0d25f40e14c2f47a43285da4faf350a01/beacon_node/rest_api/src/config.rs#L16-L24\r\n\r\nBecause both `beacon_node` programs are attempting to run with the default port (5052), the second has a collision and crashes. You can run the second with `--api-port <no-5052>` as a quick fix.\r\n\r\nMore importantly, the way `--api` command line option is configured, you can't actually turn the rest api server _off_ because this value defaults to `enabled` when no param is given. When the param is given, `--api` just triggers it to be on, so it's on always.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nShould be able to just run the commands in the quickstart without error. The quickfix is to just add an `--api-port` command to the quickstart step 3. \r\n\r\nThe deeper fix is to reconsider how the rest api should be controlled.\r\n\r\nShould probably do one of the following:\r\n- `--api` should accept True/False\r\n- `--api` should be swapped for a flag that disables the api server (eg `--no-api` or `--api-off`)\r\n- the API server should be turned off by default with the `--api` flag turning it on\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n- fix quickstart instructions\r\n- fix up `--api` so it can actually be turned on and off\r\n\r\nPlease describe the steps required to resolve this issue, if known.\r\n",
